Sentencas: By synthesizing reactive powders via a self-sustaining combustion synthesis, the EDTA-nitrate process, Sm0.15Gd0.05Ce0.8O1.9 was prepared.
Titulo: Effect of agglomeration on the densification properties of Sm0.15Gd0.05Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The resultant powders were dispersed with the terpineol as the dispersant by different methods such as ball milling and high-shear dispersing.
Titulo: Effect of agglomeration on the densification properties of Sm0.15Gd0.05Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Coagulation factor (CF) was adopted to denote the agglomeration degree of nano-scale SGDC in this work.
Titulo: Effect of agglomeration on the densification properties of Sm0.15Gd0.05Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of agglomeration on the densification behaviors at different sintering temperatures was investigated.
Titulo: Effect of agglomeration on the densification properties of Sm0.15Gd0.05Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The studies indicate that agglomeration retards densification in the stage of sintering.
Titulo: Effect of agglomeration on the densification properties of Sm0.15Gd0.05Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The powders with better dispersion exhibit a higher sintered density at the same temperature.
Titulo: Effect of agglomeration on the densification properties of Sm0.15Gd0.05Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After effective dispersion measures taken, SGDC can fully densified at the sintering temperature of 1300 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of agglomeration on the densification properties of Sm0.15Gd0.05Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The densification temperature is significantly lower than those reported previously.
Titulo: Effect of agglomeration on the densification properties of Sm0.15Gd0.05Ce0.8O1.9 electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
